cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the use of blockchain technology and smart contracts in regulating behavior over the internet, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the limitations of using code to enforce rules, which relates to machine learning (cs.LG) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The shift from "code is law" to "law is code" also involves software engineering (cs.SE) and cyber law (cs.CY).
